Lbeit it is mo undeniably evident that we are now fallen into thoſe laﬆ and mo perillous times , wherein it was foreſeen and accordingly foreſhewn ex‑ preely by the ſpirit that ſome ſhould depart from the faith 1Tim.4,1. and we ſee it veriﬁed alſo by dayly ex‑ perience men, ſometimes eminent in religion , becoming lovers of themſelves , and lovers of pleaſures more then lovers of God,and rangely mannered in every reſpe according as twas foretold they ſhould in the latter a‑ ges by Paul 2Tim.2.1,2. &c. yet I know this dorine will not be received for truth by many : nevertheleſſ I have diſcharged my conſcience as in the preſence of God,that believers therby might be put in mind to hold fa that they have, the ſuccee of which I leave to the Lord.
